<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CIVIC IMPROVEMENTS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   A developer's plan for Pier 45, presented to the San Francisco
Port Commission earlier this month, described the creation of ``San
Francisco at the Wharf.'' This $30.7 million tourist attraction
would include a 1906 ``earthquake theater'' and a ``mock Haight
Ashbury,'' an idea that was brought to the attention of veteran
Haight-Ashbury veteran  &UR; Wavy Gravy &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   ``Why not go to the regular one?'' he asked. ``It's kind of a
coexistence between the punks and the hippies, a little
cutting-edge U.N. in action.''
</P>
