<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Monday, Feb. 28 and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Mary Downes on the national-foreign desk at (206) 448-8158.
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-DEMOCRATS (Seattle) _ Vice President Al Gore met with
Boeing strikers and bashed health-care insurers Sunday on his 14th
visit to Washington since the 1996 election. Former New Jersey Sen.
Bill Bradley delivered one of his most personal and deeply felt
speeches of the campaign yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-GOP (Seattle) _ Texas Gov. George W. Bush campaigns in
Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   By Jack Hopkins. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-COLUMN-OWEN (Undated) _ I may be two riots behind in the
computer revolution. But by George, I know how to load a
dishwasher. All the spoons should be inserted in the same
compartment. When they are washed and dried, you can lift them all
out with one fist, and drop them into a drawer. Same with the
knives and forks. No sorting is necessary. We may lose the first
battles at the dishwasher. But we may win a few scrimmages at the
stove cooking up time-and-motion saving recipes like these.
</P>
<P>
   By John Owen. (Story has moved in the ``d'' category.)
</P>
</TEXT>
