<P>
   STALLED-MEMORIAL (Washington) _ Conceived as a way of giving the
5,000 black soldiers and sailors who fought in the Revolutionary
War their rightful place in the nation's history, the memorial to
honor them remains unbuilt. Now 15 years, four presidents and four
missed deadlines later, the charity created to erect the memorial
is $7 million short of the $8 million it needs by October to avoid
losing its premiere site in Washington between the Lincoln Memorial
and the Washington Monument. By Reed Abelson.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-RESEARCH (Redmond, Wash.) _ Many of the world's
computer laboratories are cutting budgets and narrowing their focus
to research that promises more immediate product applications and
financial payoffs. But Microsoft Research will grow by as much as
20 percent in the next year, and part of its work deals with
technologies that are not expected to result in products or profits
for many years. By John Markoff. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HEALTHCARE-ONLINE (Undated) _ Healtheon/WebMD has riveted
investors as its stock price rode a roller coaster while the
company announced a dizzying array of mergers and alliances to link
patients, doctors and insurers online with just about every player
in the vast industry. The plan is to promote self-help for patients
while saving untold time and money by eliminating paperwork and
insurance company phone centers. But analysts say the company must
start delivering on its promises, before investors lose confidence.
By Milt Freudenheim.
</P>
